Adam Ledezma, director of a news programme for Mundo Villa TV, a cable channel in a large slum in the centre of Argentina's capital, Buenos Aires, was stabbed to death on Saturday.Ledezma, a 33-year-old Bolivian, was also a correspondent for the newspaper Mundo Villa. He had received threats, said his wife, Ruth. Sources: Knight Centre In Spanish: Perfil/La Naci√≥n